data.title: UW Oshkosh Titan Thunder
data.meta_description: UW Oshkosh is proud to announce the premiere of two new athletic bands:Titan Thunder Marching Band and the Bolt Pep Band.
data.text:
MARCH FORWARD

A new era of Titan pride has begun! In 2022, a new University of Wisconsin Oshkosh tradition launched when the Titan Thunder Marching Band made its debut in Titan Stadium. Now an integral part of Titan game days and other events on campus and in the community, the Titan Thunder are building on a marching band legacy that reaches back more than 100 years at UWO.

Further upping the ante was the debut was the Bolt Band, the University’s pep band, built to bring a jolt of new energy and excitement to Titan basketball games inside Kolf Sports Center.

JOIN THE BAND

As a member of the UW Oshkosh athletic bands you will forge new friendships, create new UWO traditions and progress through your college career with a valuable support system. You don’t need to be a music major—both the Titan Thunder Marching Band and the Bolt Band consist of students from a variety of academic programs.
